    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Wait, this actually never worked under Windows... Just tried with grpc@1.10.0, and the same thing happens.\r\n\r\n@murgatroid99: after some manual digging, node-pre-gyp isn't even spawned. The problem is what I suspected originally: you can't do `./node_modules` under Windows. Or rather, use slashes when the command is fed into CMD directly.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7281574/43344376-5951d9fc-919e-11e8-81bc-471bf12c3099.png)\r\n\r\nSomething tells me this is an `npm` bug. If it changes command lines properly when doing anything BUT `npm ci`, something's wrong."
